OL,3,CWelsh Secretary urged to apologise
OL,4,Cover social media row
OL,6,FThe Shadow Secretary of State for
OL,7,FWales Mims Davies MP wrote to the
OL,8,FCabinet Secretary in November raising
OL,9,Fher concerns and highlighting a post
OL,10,Ffrom 20 October which read, "Today's
OL,11,FBudget has delivered for Wales for the
OL,12,Ffirst time in a generation.'
OL,14,FIt was posted by the Wales Office,
OL,15,Fwhich is a UK Government department.
OL,16,FAlthough departments are run by
OL,17,Fpoliticians and follow directions set
OL,18,Fby political party policy, they are
OL,19,Fobliged to remain neutral.
