OL,3,CWelsh Secretary urged to apologise
OL,4,Cover social media row
OL,6,FCivil service communications,
OL,7,Fincluding via social media, also have
OL,8,Fto remain neutral unlike those
OL,9,Fbelonging to individual politicians or
OL,10,Fpolitical parties.
OL,12,FIn her letter, Ms Davies wrote that,
OL,13,F"This is a blatant political statement
OL,14,Fis yet another clear breach of the
OL,15,FCivil Service Code which states: 'You
OL,16,Fmust not: act in a way that is
OL,17,Fdetermined by party-political
OL,18,Fconsiderations or use official
OL,19,Fresources for party-political
OL,20,Fpurposes."
