OL,3,CWelsh Secretary urged to apologise
OL,4,Cover social media row
OL,6,FShe went on to say that "I am sure you
OL,7,Fwill agree we simply cannot have
OL,8,Ftaxpayer-funded resources being
OL,9,Fmisappropriated on these types of
OL,10,Fmessages and your civil servants being
OL,11,Factively political inside departments,
OL,12,Fand perhaps under pressure to message
OL,13,Fthis way.
OL,15,F"Therefore can you provide me with the
OL,16,Flatest development towards launching
OL,17,Fan investigation into the Secretary of
OL,18,FState and her officials to uncover the
OL,19,Ffull details of these serious code
OL,20,Fbreaches?"
