OL,3,CWelsh Secretary urged to apologise
OL,4,Cover social media row
OL,6,FIn response, the UK Government's Chief
OL,7,FExecutive of Communications, Simon
OL,8,FBaugh, wrote to reiterate the
OL,9,Fguidelines for civil service-run
OL,10,Fsocial media accounts.
OL,12,F"The Government Communication Service
OL,13,Fhas published clear guidelines and
OL,14,Fmandatory training on the use of
OL,15,Fsocial media by civil servants,
OL,16,Fincluding on official accounts. The
OL,17,Fguidance sets out that posts on
OL,18,Fofficial accounts should not contain
OL,19,Fparty political material within the
OL,20,Fbody of the message or contained
OL,21,Fwithin links.
OL,26,@tD@AOU
