OL,3,CWelsh Secretary urged to apologise
OL,4,Cover social media row
OL,6,F"We now need the Secretary of State
OL,7,Ffor Wales to step up and apologise for
OL,8,Fthis conduct in politicising our
OL,9,Fimpartial civil servants and then
OL,10,Ffocus her energy on actually
OL,11,Fdelivering something for the people of
OL,12,FWales."
OL,14,FA Wales Office spokesperson said, "The
OL,15,FWales Office follows guidance set out
OL,16,Fby the Government Communication
OL,17,FService and mandatory training is
OL,18,Fundertaken on the use of social media
OL,19,Fon official government channels.
